{"TopicId":30090,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Role of girders","CreatedByName":"Mantis Toboggan","CreatedById":61379,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:12:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mantis Toboggan","CreatedById":61379,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:12:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhenever I look at the structural parts tab, I always see them, but what is the point of using the large girders?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fiddlestyx","CreatedById":57329,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:35:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThey make great solar panel arrays.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/dkwWr4g.png\u0022 alt=\u0022dkwWr4g.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Warscribe","CreatedById":58388,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:46:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ESpines for your infiniglide.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v699/BlackAnti/screenshot50_zpsa2ba8465.png~original\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot50_zpsa2ba8465.png~original\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PaleoGamer","CreatedById":66992,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:49:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOffsetting your docking ports for one...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://cloud-2.steampowered.com/ugc/882983254888205943/6314651B8F298AD578D43A9729AC81B7B34EFF7B/\u0022 alt=\u00226314651B8F298AD578D43A9729AC81B7B34EFF7B\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shrike42","CreatedById":61104,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:51:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThey let you make pretty much everything radial mounted, and allow you to get extra distance and structural strength into your designs without that much additional weight.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rodion_herrera","CreatedById":66284,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:53:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIf you know how to flip them or do incremental, small angle adjusts, you can build just about anything with them. Without the long and short girders, I wouldn\u0027t have been able to mount my intakes they way they are attached in this screenshot:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img843.imageshack.us/img843/2461/screenshot204m.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot204m.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-29T21:56:14Z\u0022 title=\u002205/29/2013 09:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 29, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by rodion_herrera\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Destroyer","CreatedById":36109,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:56:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThey make AMAZING landing legs. They have Uber crash tolerance, so even a 100 m/s dive to the ground can be stopped with 3 of the long ones.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Camelotking524","CreatedById":58776,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T21:58:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EUltimate Correct Answer: Whatever your imagination can come up with\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOT: Howdy Destroyer.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CalculusWarrior","CreatedById":58313,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T23:03:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDanny2462 managed to use them to destroy a planet: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/NLscXyIP4c8?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you can\u0027t think of any use for them, that option is always open \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T23:09:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ERover suspensions: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ulKrobJ.png\u0022 alt=\u0022ulKrobJ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"llamatoes","CreatedById":57750,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-29T23:10:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI use them to create tail planes, as it means that on your infiniglider, you get to put your centre of lift back with practically no weight lost.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}